1
00:00:00,270 --> 00:00:04,000
First group, those who surrendered completely.

2
00:00:04,750 --> 00:00:10,241
The majority of people are convinced deep down inside that they haven't got what it takes,

3
00:00:10,351 --> 00:00:17,921
that real success, real accomplishment, is for others who are lucky or fortunate in some special respect.

4
00:00:18,351 --> 00:00:27,281
You can easily spot these people because they go to great lengths to rationalize their status and explain how happy they really are.

5
00:00:28,190 --> 00:00:35,440
A very intelligent man, age 32, who has dead-ended himself in a safe but mediocre position,

6
00:00:35,710 --> 00:00:40,721
recently spent hours telling me why he was so satisfied with his job.

7
00:00:40,991 --> 00:00:46,161
He did a good job of rationalizing, but he was only kidding himself and he knew it.

8
00:00:46,431 --> 00:00:52,080
What he really wanted was to work in a challenging situation where he could grow and develop.

9
00:00:52,431 --> 00:00:59,440
but that multitude of suppressive influences had convinced him that he was inadequate for big things.

10
00:00:59,950 --> 00:01:07,521
This group is, in reality, just the other extreme of the discontented job-switcher searching for opportunity.

11
00:01:08,030 --> 00:01:15,281
Rationalizing yourself into a rut, which, incidentally, has been described as a grave with both ends open,

12
00:01:15,471 --> 00:01:22,721
can be as bad as wandering aimlessly, hoping opportunity will somehow, someday, hit you in the face.

13
00:01:24,750 --> 00:01:25,760
Second group.

14
00:01:26,270 --> 00:01:28,880
Those who surrendered partially.

15
00:01:29,390 --> 00:01:35,121
A second but much smaller group enters adult life with considerable hope for success.

16
00:01:35,471 --> 00:01:37,440
These people prepare themselves.

17
00:01:37,551 --> 00:01:38,320
They work.

18
00:01:38,431 --> 00:01:39,281
They plan.

19
00:01:39,471 --> 00:01:43,361
But after a decade or so, resistance begins to build up.

20
00:01:43,551 --> 00:01:46,721
Competition for top-level jobs looks rugged.

21
00:01:46,991 --> 00:01:51,440
This group then decides that greater success is not worth the effort.

22
00:01:51,710 --> 00:01:57,041
They rationalize, we're earning more than the average and we live better than the average.

23
00:01:57,150 --> 00:01:59,200
Why should we knock ourselves out?

24
00:01:59,551 --> 00:02:03,041
Actually, this group has developed a set of fears.

25
00:02:03,231 --> 00:02:10,320
Fear of failure, fear of social disapproval, fear of insecurity, fear of losing what they already have.

26
00:02:10,830 --> 00:02:16,000
These people aren't satisfied because deep down they know they have surrendered.

27
00:02:16,270 --> 00:02:25,041
This group includes many talented, intelligent people who elect to crawl through life because they are afraid to stand up and run.
